      <!-- ********** Main content ********** --> 
      <h1>Welcome</h1> 
      <p>UC Berkeley has been fully accredited since 1949 and had its <a href="/accreditation/index.html">accreditation reaffirmed most recently in 2004</a>. The campus is currently in its next cycle of accreditation as part of the second cohort of institutions accredited under <a href="http://www.wascsenior.org/">WASC</a>’s pilot of its new institutional review process. The focus of the process is on the meaning, quality and integrity of degrees; evidence of student learning at all degree levels, emphasizing undergraduates’ skills acquisition; undergraduate graduation and retention rates; and institutional sustainability and strategic planning for the future.</p> 
      <h2>Current Review Schedule</h2> 
      <table class="datatable"> 
       <tbody>
        <tr> 
         <th scope="row">September 2012 to August 2013</th> 
         <td>Preparation of Institutional Narrative and Data Exhibits</td> 
        </tr> 
        <tr> 
         <th scope="row">August 23, 2013</th> 
         <td>Institutional Narrative and Data Exhibits submitted to WASC</td> 
        </tr> 
        <tr> 
         <th scope="row">October 31, 2013</th> 
         <td>Off Site Review</td> 
        </tr> 
        <tr> 
         <th scope="row">October 22-24, 2014</th> 
         <td>Accreditation Visit</td> 
        </tr> 
        <tr> 
         <th scope="row"><span style="font-weight:bold">February 19, 2015</span></th> 
         <td><span style="font-weight:bold">WASC Commission Meeting</span></td> 
        </tr> 
       </tbody>
      </table> 
      <h2>Peer Review Team</h2> 
      <ul> 
       <li>Team Chair: Mary Sue Coleman, President Emeritus, University of Michigan</li> 
       <li>Team Assistant Chair: Christopher Cullander, Director (Retired), Office of Institutional Research, University of California San Francisco</li> 
       <li>David Fairris, Professor of Economics, University of California, Riverside</li> 
       <li>Maryann Jacobi Gray, Assistant Provost, University of California, Los Angeles</li> 
       <li>Jillian Kinzie, Associate Director, IU Center for Postsecondary Research and NSSE Institute, Indiana University Bloomington</li> 
       <li>Laura E. Martin, Coordinator for Institutional Assessment, University of California, Merced</li> 
       <li>Brad Osgood (off-site review only), Senior Associate Dean for Student Affairs, School of Engineering, Stanford University</li> 
      </ul> 
      <p>Questions or comments about the UC Berkeley institutional accreditation may be directed to Accreditation Liaison Officer Cynthia Schrager at <a href="mailto:berkeleyalo@lists.berkeley.edu">berkeleyalo@lists.berkeley.edu</a>.</p> 
